<script>
  // === Branding (START SOLUTION) ===
  const BRAND_LOGO_SRC = "data:image/png;base64,"; // dejar este PNG en la misma carpeta del HTML

  // Modelos (tomado de tu listado)
  const MODEL_LIST = [
    ["P-8 960×960 Outdoor", {mw:960, mh:960, pitch:8.0, type:"Outdoor"}],
    ["P-6.66 960×960 Outdoor", {mw:960, mh:960, pitch:6.66, type:"Outdoor"}],
    ["P-5 960×960 Outdoor", {mw:960, mh:960, pitch:5.0, type:"Outdoor"}],
    ["P-4 960×960 Outdoor", {mw:960, mh:960, pitch:4.0, type:"Outdoor"}],
    ["P-4 960×960 Indoor", {mw:960, mh:960, pitch:4.0, type:"Indoor"}],
    ["P-4 640×480 Indoor", {mw:640, mh:480, pitch:4.0, type:"Indoor"}],
    ["P-3.9 500×1000 Rental Outdoor", {mw:500, mh:1000, pitch:3.9, type:"Outdoor", casePanels:6}],
    ["P-3.9 500×500 Rental Outdoor", {mw:500, mh:500, pitch:3.9, type:"Outdoor", casePanels:8}],
    ["P-3.9 500×1000 Rental Indoor", {mw:500, mh:1000, pitch:3.9, type:"Indoor"}],
    ["P-3.03 960×960 Indoor", {mw:960, mh:960, pitch:3.03, type:"Indoor"}],
    ["P-3.03 640×480 Indoor", {mw:640, mh:480, pitch:3.03, type:"Indoor"}],
    ["P-2.9 500×1000 Outdoor", {mw:500, mh:1000, pitch:2.9, type:"Outdoor"}],
    ["P-2.5 640×480 Indoor", {mw:640, mh:480, pitch:2.5, type:"Indoor"}],
    ["P-1.8 640×480 Indoor", {mw:640, mh:480, pitch:1.8, type:"Indoor"}],
  ["P-1.5 640×480 Indoor", {mw:640, mh:480, pitch:1.5, type:"Indoor"}],
  ];
  const MODELS = Object.fromEntries(MODEL_LIST);

  // UI init
  const moduleSelect = document.getElementById("moduleType");
  MODEL_LIST.forEach(([name]) => {
    const o = document.createElement("option");
    o.value = name;
    o.textContent = name;
    moduleSelect.appendChild(o);
  });
  moduleSelect.value = "P-5 960×960 Outdoor";

  // Auto recalcular al cambiar modelo (mejor UX en móvil)
  moduleSelect.addEventListener("change", ()=>{ try{ calculate(); }catch(e){ console.error(e); } });

  function byMetersToModules(wM, hM, cfg){
    const wMm = wM * 1000, hMm = hM * 1000;
    return {
      cols: Math.max(1, Math.round(wMm / cfg.mw)),
      rows: Math.max(1, Math.round(hMm / cfg.mh)),
    };
  }

  function parseWH(txt){
    const t = (txt || "").toLowerCase().replace(/\s+/g,"").replace("×","x");
    const [w,h] = t.split("x").map(n => parseInt(n) || 0);
    return { maxW: w || 3840, maxH: h || 3840 };
  }

  // Consumo: Outdoor ref 5000 nits ~ 900 W/m², Indoor ref 1500 nits ~ 450 W/m²
  // Se escala linealmente con el brillo. Promedio ≈ 35% del pico.
  function powerFor(model, areaM2, nits){
    const isOutdoor = (model.type||"").toLowerCase().includes("outdoor");
    const refNits = isOutdoor ? 5000 : 1500;
    const refWm2 = isOutdoor ? 900 : 450;
    const ratio = Math.max(0.05, Math.min(1, nits / refNits));
    const Wm2 = refWm2 * ratio;
    const W_peak = Math.round(Wm2 * areaM2);
    const W_avg = Math.round(W_peak * 0.35);
    return { W_peak, W_avg };
  }

  // Térmicas sugeridas (mono @220V y tri @380V, PF=0.9)
  function breakerSuggest(W_peak){
    const std = [10,16,20,25,32,40,50,63,80,100];
    const Vmono = 220, Vtri = 380, PF = 0.9;
    const I_mono = W_peak / Vmono;
    const monoA = std.find(a => I_mono <= a) || std[std.length-1];
    const mono_label = `Monofásica: térmica ${monoA}A @ 220V (pico ≈ ${I_mono.toFixed(1)}A)`;

    const I_tri = W_peak / (Math.sqrt(3) * Vtri * PF);
    const triA = std.find(a => I_tri <= a) || std[std.length-1];
    const tri_label = `Trifásica: térmica ${triA}A (pico ≈ ${I_tri.toFixed(1)}A @ 380V, PF 0.9)`;

    const exceedsMono = I_mono > 32;
    return { I_mono, I_tri, monoA, triA, mono_label, tri_label, exceedsMono };
  }

  function safeModelKey(m){
    return m.replace(/\s+/g,'_').replace(/×/g,'x').replace(/[^\w\-]/g,'');
  }
  function nameFrom(last){
    const m = safeModelKey(last.modelKey);
    const w = Number(last.totalWm).toFixed(2);
    const h = Number(last.totalHm).toFixed(2);
    return `Plano_${m}_${w}x${h}m`;
  }

  // Logo image
  const brandLogo = new Image();
  brandLogo.src = BRAND_LOGO_SRC;

  let last = null;

  function calculate(){
    const modelKey = moduleSelect.value;
    const cfg = MODELS[modelKey];

    const mode = document.getElementById("inputMode").value;
    const pxPerOut = Math.max(100000, parseInt(document.getElementById("pxPerOut").value) || 650000);
    const {maxW, maxH} = parseWH(document.getElementById("maxWH").value);
    const nits = Math.max(300, parseInt(document.getElementById("brightness").value) || 1500);

    let cols, rows;
    if(mode === "meters"){
      const wM = parseFloat(document.getElementById("widthM").value) || 1;
      const hM = parseFloat(document.getElementById("heightM").value) || 1;
      const cr = byMetersToModules(wM, hM, cfg);
      cols = cr.cols; rows = cr.rows;
    } else {
      cols = Math.max(1, parseInt(document.getElementById("width").value) || 1);
      rows = Math.max(1, parseInt(document.getElementById("height").value) || 1);
    }

    const totalWmm = cols * cfg.mw, totalHmm = rows * cfg.mh;
    const totalWm = +(totalWmm / 1000).toFixed(2);
    const totalHm = +(totalHmm / 1000).toFixed(2);
    const area = +(totalWm * totalHm).toFixed(2);

    const pxW = Math.round(totalWmm / cfg.pitch);
    const pxH = Math.round(totalHmm / cfg.pitch);
    const pixels = pxW * pxH;

    const needByPixels = Math.max(1, Math.ceil(pixels / pxPerOut));
    const needByW = Math.max(1, Math.ceil(pxW / maxW));
    const needByH = Math.max(1, Math.ceil(pxH / maxH));
    const outputs = Math.max(needByPixels, needByW, needByH);

    let rec = "";
    if(outputs <= 1) rec = "1 salida: TB1 / TB2 (NovaStar) o MSD300";
    else if(outputs === 2) rec = "2 salidas: Serie Taurus (TB3–TB6) o 2×MSD300/MSD600";
    else if(outputs <= 4) rec = `${outputs} salidas: considerar VX600 (o 2×MSD600)`;
    else rec = `${outputs} salidas: considerar VX1000 (o múltiples VX600)`;

    const {W_peak, W_avg} = powerFor(cfg, area, nits);
    const b = breakerSuggest(W_peak);

    last = { modelKey, cfg, cols, rows, totalWm, totalHm, area, pxW, pxH, pixels, outputs, rec, pxPerOut, maxW, maxH, nits, W_peak, W_avg, breaker: b };
    render();
  }

  function render(){
    if(!last) return;

    const grid = document.getElementById("grid");
    grid.innerHTML = "";

    const lines = [
      ["Modelo", last.modelKey],
      ["Tamaño panel (mm)", `${last.cfg.mw} × ${last.cfg.mh}`],
      ["Pitch (mm)", String(last.cfg.pitch)],
      ["Módulos (ancho × alto)", `${last.cols} × ${last.rows}`],
      ["Dimensiones (m)", `${last.totalWm} × ${last.totalHm}`],
      ["Área (m²)", String(last.area)],
      ["Resolución (px)", `${last.pxW} × ${last.pxH}`],
      ["Píxeles totales", last.pixels.toLocaleString()],
      ["Outputs estimados", String(last.outputs)],
      ["Sugerencia de envío/procesador", last.rec],
      ["Brillo objetivo (nits)", String(last.nits)],
      ["Consumo promedio (W)", last.W_avg.toLocaleString()],
      ["Consumo pico (W)", last.W_peak.toLocaleString()],
      ["Térmica monofásica", last.breaker.mono_label + (last.breaker.exceedsMono ? " • Excede 32A, preferir trifásica" : "")],
      ["Térmica trifásica", last.breaker.tri_label],
      ["Límites por salida (px)", `${last.maxW} × ${last.maxH}; ${last.pxPerOut.toLocaleString()} px`],
    ];

    for(const [k,v] of lines){
      const el = document.createElement("div");
      el.className = "kv";
      el.innerHTML = `<b>${k}</b><span>${v}</span>`;
      grid.appendChild(el);
    }

    document.getElementById("result").style.display = "block";
    document.getElementById("diagramCard").style.display = "block";
    drawDiagram();
  }

  function clamp(x,a,b){ return Math.max(a, Math.min(b, x)); }

  


function drawDiagram(){
  const cvs = document.getElementById("diagram");
  const parentW = Math.max(320, ((cvs.parentElement && cvs.parentElement.clientWidth) || 800) - 2);
  const baseH = Math.max(380, Math.round(parentW * 0.64));
  const dpr = Math.max(1, window.devicePixelRatio || 1);

  cvs.width = Math.round(parentW * dpr);
  cvs.height = Math.round(baseH * dpr);
  cvs.style.width = parentW + "px";
  cvs.style.height = baseH + "px";

  const ctx = cvs.getContext("2d");
  ctx.setTransform(1,0,0,1,0,0);
  ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
  ctx.clearRect(0,0,parentW,baseH);

  const clamp = (x,a,b)=>Math.max(a, Math.min(b, x));
  const roundRect = (x,y,w,h,r)=>{
    r = Math.min(r, w/2, h/2);
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(x+r,y);
    ctx.arcTo(x+w,y,x+w,y+h,r);
    ctx.arcTo(x+w,y+h,x,y+h,r);
    ctx.arcTo(x,y+h,x,y,r);
    ctx.arcTo(x,y,x+w,y,r);
    ctx.closePath();
  };

  // Background
  ctx.fillStyle = "#070F1A";
  ctx.fillRect(0,0,parentW,baseH);

  if(!last) return;

  // Header (model + resolution) — auto scales to avoid overlap
  const headerY = 22;
  const headerMaxW = parentW - 24;
  const modelTxt = String(last.modelKey || "").trim();
  const resTxtHeader = `${last.pxW}×${last.pxH} px`;

  // Fit model line
  let f1 = clamp(parentW * 0.024, 13, 16);
  ctx.textAlign = "center";
  ctx.textBaseline = "top";
  ctx.fillStyle = "#CFE2FF";
  while(f1 > 12){
    ctx.font = `800 ${f1}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
    if(ctx.measureText(modelTxt).width <= headerMaxW) break;
    f1 -= 1;
  }
  // Fit resolution line
  let f2 = clamp(f1 * 0.76, 11, 14);
  ctx.fillStyle = "#9FB1C7";
  while(f2 > 10){
    ctx.font = `700 ${f2}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
    if(ctx.measureText(resTxtHeader).width <= headerMaxW) break;
    f2 -= 1;
  }

  // Reserve vertical space so dimensions + screen never collide with header
  const headerH = (f1 + 2) + (f2 + 2) + 10;

  // Draw header background pill for readability (subtle)
  const pillW = Math.min(headerMaxW, Math.max(ctx.measureText(modelTxt).width, ctx.measureText(resTxtHeader).width) + 32);
  const pillH = headerH - 6;
  const pillX = (parentW - pillW) / 2;
  const pillY = headerY - 8;

  ctx.save();
  ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(5,10,18,0.38)";
  ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(28,42,62,0.35)";
  ctx.lineWidth = 1;
  roundRect(pillX, pillY, pillW, pillH, 14);
  ctx.fill();
  roundRect(pillX, pillY, pillW, pillH, 14);
  ctx.stroke();

  // Model
  ctx.fillStyle = "#CFE2FF";
  ctx.font = `800 ${f1}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
  ctx.fillText(modelTxt, parentW/2, headerY);
  // Resolution
  ctx.fillStyle = "#9FB1C7";
  ctx.font = `700 ${f2}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
  ctx.fillText(resTxtHeader, parentW/2, headerY + f1 + 10);
  ctx.restore();
const mw = last.cfg.mw, mh = last.cfg.mh;
  const cols = last.cols, rows = last.rows;
  const gridWmm = cols * mw, gridHmm = rows * mh;

  // margins: keep dimensions OUTSIDE and footer clean
  const M = clamp(Math.min(parentW, baseH) * 0.12, 64, 116);
  const left = M, top = M + headerH, right = Math.round(M * 0.70), bottom = Math.round(M * 1.05);

  const availW = parentW - left - right;
  const availH = baseH - top - bottom;

  const scale = Math.min(availW / gridWmm, availH / gridHmm);
  const gridPxW = gridWmm * scale;
  const gridPxH = gridHmm * scale;

  const ox = left + (availW - gridPxW) / 2;
  const oy = top + (availH - gridPxH) / 2;

  const cellW = mw * scale;
  const cellH = mh * scale;

  // Panels with clear separation (NO text inside each panel)
  const gap = clamp(Math.round(Math.min(cellW, cellH) * 0.06), 2, 7);
  const innerW = Math.max(1, cellW - gap);
  const innerH = Math.max(1, cellH - gap);

  // outer frame
  ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(207,226,255,0.38)";
  ctx.lineWidth = 2;
  ctx.strokeRect(ox - 1, oy - 1, gridPxW + 2, gridPxH + 2);

  for(let r=0; r<rows; r++){
    for(let c=0; c<cols; c++){
      const x = ox + c * cellW;
      const y = oy + r * cellH;

      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(180,200,220,0.035)";
      ctx.fillRect(x + gap/2, y + gap/2, innerW, innerH);

      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(207,226,255,0.22)";
      ctx.lineWidth = 1.1;
      ctx.strokeRect(x + gap/2, y + gap/2, innerW, innerH);
    }
  }

  // Watermark logo (centered, adaptive)
  if(typeof brandLogo !== "undefined" && brandLogo.complete){
    const nw = brandLogo.naturalWidth || brandLogo.width || 1;
    const nh = brandLogo.naturalHeight || brandLogo.height || 1;
    const ratio = nh / nw;

    const base = Math.min(gridPxW, gridPxH);
    const lw = clamp(base * 0.72, 160, gridPxW * 0.94);
    const lh = lw * ratio;
    const lx = ox + (gridPxW - lw) / 2;
    const ly = oy + (gridPxH - lh) / 2;

    ctx.save();
    ctx.globalAlpha = 0.18;
    ctx.drawImage(brandLogo, lx, ly, lw, lh);
    ctx.restore();
  }

  // Dimension lines (outside)
  const dimOff = clamp(M * 0.40, 22, 44);
  ctx.strokeStyle = "#9FB1C7";
  ctx.fillStyle = "#9FB1C7";
  ctx.lineWidth = 1.1;

  // width top
  ctx.beginPath();
  ctx.moveTo(ox, oy - dimOff);
  ctx.lineTo(ox + gridPxW, oy - dimOff);
  ctx.stroke();

  ctx.font = `${clamp(M*0.22, 13, 16)}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
  ctx.textAlign = "center";
  ctx.textBaseline = "bottom";
  ctx.fillText(`${last.totalWm} m`, ox + gridPxW/2, oy - dimOff - 4);

  // height left
  ctx.beginPath();
  ctx.moveTo(ox - dimOff, oy);
  ctx.lineTo(ox - dimOff, oy + gridPxH);
  ctx.stroke();

  ctx.save();
  ctx.translate(ox - dimOff - 8, oy + gridPxH/2);
  ctx.rotate(-Math.PI/2);
  ctx.textAlign = "center";
  ctx.textBaseline = "bottom";
  ctx.fillText(`${last.totalHm} m`, 0, 0);
  ctx.restore();

  
  // Footer info — auto-fit and never overlap
  const footerY = baseH - 20;
  const areaTxt = `${last.area} m²`;
  const sizeTxt = `${last.totalWm}×${last.totalHm} m`;
  const resLine = `${last.pxW}×${last.pxH} px`;
  const modTxt = `${last.cols}×${last.rows} (${last.cols*last.rows})`;

  const rightTxt = "© START SOLUTION — offline";
  const leftX = left;
  const rightX = parentW - right;

  // Right label
  ctx.textBaseline = "alphabetic";
  ctx.textAlign = "right";
  ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(124,143,168,0.9)";
  ctx.font = "11px system-ui, sans-serif";
  ctx.fillText(rightTxt, rightX, footerY);

  const rightW = ctx.measureText(rightTxt).width;
  const maxLeftW = Math.max(120, (rightX - 14) - leftX - rightW); // keep a gap

  // Left block (prefer 1 line; fallback to 2 lines)
  const line1 = `Modelo: ${modelTxt}  •  Resolución: ${resLine}`;
  const line2 = `Medida: ${sizeTxt}  •  Área: ${areaTxt}  •  Módulos: ${modTxt}`;

  let f = 13;
  ctx.textAlign = "left";
  ctx.fillStyle = "#7C8FA8";

  const fits = (fontPx, a, b) => {
    ctx.font = `${fontPx}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
    return (ctx.measureText(a).width <= maxLeftW) && (ctx.measureText(b).width <= maxLeftW);
  };

  // try to fit in two lines (always safe), but if line2 is short, line1 might still be okay
  while(f > 10 && !fits(f, line1, line2)) f -= 1;

  ctx.font = `${f}px system-ui, sans-serif`;
  ctx.fillText(line1, leftX, footerY - 14);
  ctx.fillText(line2, leftX, footerY);
}
